  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Purpose&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This metric is used to help the team understand whether they are addressing stakeholder change requests. Monitoring the&#xD;
    number of change requests that have not been approved also supports planning activities and risk management.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Definition&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Count the number change requests that have not been approved in the reporting period. Divide this number by the total&#xD;
    number of&amp;nbsp;open change requests.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Analysis&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A good way to monitor&amp;nbsp;the Percentage of Unapproved Change Requests&amp;nbsp;is to use a simple bar chart. Plot&#xD;
    iterations on the X axis and percentage on the Y axis.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Confirm&amp;nbsp;there is a reasonable percentage of unapproved change requests. Too many unapproved change requests can&#xD;
    result in:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Delays in implementing needed changes, and high cost to implement&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Low customer satisfaction levels&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Confirm that the team's change management process is used consistently and that efficient tools are in place to support&#xD;
    the process.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Frequency and reporting&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Change request states are tracked throughout the lifecycle as they occur. The project manager should monitor trends,&#xD;
    and when problems arise should review with the team during iteration assessments.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Collection and reporting tools&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; ClearQuest&amp;reg; and IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Team Concert&amp;reg; collect change request data.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
